commit_message:
Analyze the data in step2_output.tsv

This R script will provide the following graphical analysis of the data contained in step2_output.tsv:

-A box and whisker plot showing the distribution of gene lengths in each genome (along with an appropriate test of statistical significance for the difference in the medians).
-A table displaying the number of genes in each level-2 Enzyme Commission category for each of the two genomes.
-A bar plot showing a comparison of the counts of genes in each genome in each of the level-2 EC categories (also a second bar plot with the counts transformed to percentages).
Data extracted from step2.pl organized as TSV

Query the db for specific data and output to file

The following Perl script can be run to extract a specific subset of data from the gpls718project database that was created earlier using SQL queries.

Loads annotation data into db.

This Perl script can be run to parse the data in the trach.annotation and ecoli.annotation and load those data into the gpls718project database created and instantiated by the gpls718project.sql file.

Instantiates db to store genome annotation data

This SQL code can be used to instantiate a database that will hold the data contained in the trach.annotation and ecoli.annotation files.

C. trachomatis genome annotation

This is a tab delimited text file containing annotation data gathered from the sequence analysis of the C. trachomatis genome.

E. Coli genome annotation

This is a tab delimited text file containing annotation data gathered from the sequence analysis of the E. coli genome.
